description: Gnostice XtremeDocumentStudio .NET Multi-format HTML5 Document Viewer is the next-generation multi-format document-viewing technology for .NET developers. The DocumentViewer control supports viewing, form-filling, text searching (with OCR support) and printing PDF, DOCX, DOC, TXT, BMP, JPEG, PNG, WMF, EMF, and single-page and multi-page TIFF. It works on both desktop(Windows 7, Windows 8.1, Windows 10, Linux, Mac OS X) and mobile browsers (IOS, Android, Windows Phone).
releaseNotes:
Version 2016 R5 - August 4, 2016
================================
Enhanced
~~~~~~~~
+ HTML5 Document Viewer
  - Interactive form filling
    * Introduced keyboard navigation support
    * Text Field
      + Support for “SpellCheck” property
      + Support for “DoNotScroll” property on single line Text Fields
    * ListBox and ComboBox
      + Support for selection of multiple items
    * Radio Button
      + Support for “RadioInUnison” property
    * Introduced “highlightColor” under “Preferences” to set the preferred highlight color for form fields
    * Grouped all form fields related options under “Preferences”:
      + Preferences.InteractiveElements.FormFields.enableFormFilling
      + Preferences.InteractiveElements.FormFields.highlightColor
    * Improved form filling experience by making field highlight region transparent to avoid masking of page background
  - Introduced “save()” API to save the form field changes on the server
  - Introduced “beforeDocumentSave” and “afterDocumentSave” events
+ Multi-Format Document Viewers / Printer / Converter 
  - PDF Viewing, Conversion and Printing
    * Support for AES 256-bit encrypted PDF documents

Fixed
~~~~~
+ PDF Engine
  - Form fields with flags such as “Hidden” and “NoView” were rendered while viewing and printing the page contents.
